  "text": "SQUIDs with Josephson junctions [CITATION_1] . To realize largescale quantum computing systems, an efficient control of the superconducting phase in Josephson junctions needs to be achieved. In currently developed superconducting qubits, the phases of the Josephson junctions are primarily controlled by external magnetic fields. This approach is suitable when only a few qubits are used. However, a more efficient approach needs to be developed for large-scale systems because it is difficult to precisely control many qubit phases owing to the variations in physical parameters in the qubits.",
  "correct_citation": {
